00:01:21.376 --> 00:01:23.243
So I'm just gonna
restate the product rule.

00:01:23.243 --> 00:01:25.032
This is going to be
equal to the derivative

00:01:25.032 --> 00:01:26.562
of the first function,

00:01:26.562 --> 00:01:27.645
f prime of x,

00:01:28.795 --> 00:01:32.674
times the second function,
not taking its derivative.

00:01:32.674 --> 00:01:35.535
Plus the first function,
not taking its derivative,

00:01:35.535 --> 00:01:38.773
f of x, times the derivative
of the second function,

00:01:38.773 --> 00:01:39.856
h prime of x.

00:01:40.734 --> 00:01:43.022
So if you're trying to
find g prime of three,

00:01:43.022 --> 00:01:44.747
